1.	Crypto-Currency is a digital currency in which encryption techniques are used to regulate the generation of units of currency and verify operating independently of a Central Bank.
2.	As of February 2020, there are over 1600 cryptocurrencies in circulation and growing. ‘Bitcoin’ currently the largest blockchain network, followed by ‘Ripple’, ‘Ethereum’ and ‘Tether’.
3.	As of December 2018, the total crypto currency market capitalization is 100 billion dollars and larger than GDP of 127 countries.
    **Dollar 1000 invested in ‘Bitcoin’ on 02nd March 2012 would be worth Dollar 1 million on 21st October 2017 (i.e., Five and half years and 1000x returns!)**
4.	The decentralized control of each cryptocurrency works through distributes ledger technology, typically a blockchain that serves as a public financial transaction database.
5.	Cryptocurrencies are used primarily outside existing banking and governmental institutions and are exchanged over the internet.
6.	Reference data to be downloaded from “INVESTING.COM”.
